events.name: A speed tour of Google for developers by Rupert Whitehead
events.description:
Join us for the next Google Developer Group / GDG Cardiff meetup!

Hope everyone had a wonderful Christmas / New Year break.  We're back in action for the 16th of February, fresh from the Google Developer Conference in London with a very special guest speaker Rupert Whitehead.  

Rupert Whitehead

Developer Relations Programs Lead, UK & Ireland, Google 

Rupert helps make developers more successful with Google's technologies. This covers a broad range of areas ranging from web, android and cloud to apps script, YouTube and maps. He's also leading the agencies program in Europe.

Talk: A speed tour of Google for developers

Google Developer Relations covers a wide range of technologies that can help developers. Rupert will give an overview of Google's approach to developer communities and a speed tour of hot tech topics as we look ahead through 2017. There should be lots of time for questions and answers.

We've got just the one speaker this month - giving plenty of opportunities for Q&A afterwards.

Our sponsors this month are Nagra Media UK and Acorn Recruitment

We'll be welcoming people from 17:00, giving you a chance to network with other developers from around Cardiff.  The talks won't start until 17:45 - 18:00 though, so don't worry if you can't make it until a little later.  Once our speakers have finished we'll head across to a pub for a couple of drinks and a chat about the evening.

events.name: Google Developer Group (GDG) Cardiff - April
events.description:
Join us for the next Google Developer Group / GDG Cardiff!

We've had a month off to recouperate while the whole team has been super busy, but we've sorted an extra special speaker all the way from Seattle, USA for you this month!

Laurence Moroney

Google Developer Advocate

Laurence is the author of more programming books than he'd care to count, as well as the popular 'Fourth World' series of Young Adult Novels, as well as a comic book author. He's a staff Developer Advocate at Google, working on Firebase and the Google Maps platforms. As a graduate of the University of Wales in Cardiff, and having spent much of his childhood there, he's really excited to speak at GDG Cardiff about Firebase!

Talk: Google Firebase, why, what, how?

At Google we've been doing a lot of research into the habits of highly successful developers. This leads us to build developer products with the aim of helping you follow those habits. Laurence will talk about the Firebase suite, taking you through the why as well as the what, and show how you to get started building, growing and earning from your hard work!

We've got just the one speaker again this month - giving plenty of opportunities for Q&A afterwards in the library and at the pub too!

Our sponsors this month are Nagra Media UK and Acorn Recruitment

We'll be welcoming people from 17:00, giving you a chance to network with other developers from around Cardiff.  The talks won't start until 17:45 - 18:00 though, so don't worry if you can't make it until a little later.  Once our speakers have finished we'll head across to a pub for a couple of drinks and a chat about the evening.
events.how_to_find_us: We're on the top floor of the library, ask at reception and they'll point you our way

events.name: Google Developer Group (GDG) Cardiff - I/O Extended
events.description:
Join us for the next Google Developer Group / GDG Cardiff!

This month is a little different as we will be running (for the first time!) an I/O Extended event. We will be live streaming the Google I/O keynote from Mountain View, CA. This is a first for us, but also for Wales!

I/O Extended is a great way of bringing our local development community together to experience the keynote in real-time while exchanging ideas. Google regards I/O as its key event of the year, so we are expecting some big announcements. Last year we had Daydream, Home, and Android N to name a few.

To give a little insight into I/O 2017, here's a great highlights video from 2016:

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QPhXL1Im7ds

Refreshments will be provided as always, so pop along and find out all the latest together.

Our sponsors this month are Nagra Media UK (https://www.nagra.com/) and Acorn Recruitment (http://www.acornpeople.com/)

We'll be welcoming people from 17:00, giving you a chance to network with other developers and grab a seat. The live stream won't start until 18:00, but don't worry if you can't make it until a little later. You are more than welcome to join us anytime between 17:00 and 20:00. Once the I/O keynotes have finished we'll head across to a pub for a couple of drinks and a chat about the evening.
events.how_to_find_us: We're on the top floor of the library, ask at reception and they'll point you our way

events.name: Google Developer Group (GDG) Cardiff - October
events.description:
Join us for the next Google Developer Group / GDG Cardiff!

We've had the summer off to recouperate while the whole team has been super busy, but we've been lucky to get back an extra special speaker, returning from sunny Seattle, USA.

Laurence Moroney

Google Developer Advocate Laurence is the author of more programming books than he'd care to count, as well as the popular 'Fourth World' series of Young Adult Novels, as well as a comic book author. He's a staff Developer Advocate at Google, working on Firebase and the Google Maps platforms. As a graduate of the University of Wales in Cardiff, and having spent much of his childhood there, he's really excited to return to GDG Cardiff!

Talk: How I survived writing Cloud Functions for Firebase

Having come from a programming world where server side code was explicitly managed, explicitly deployed and explicitly called, moving to a serverless environment was a bit of a mindshift. In this talk Laurence will introduce you to Cloud Functions for Firebase, and how they work in a serverless environment where they get triggered based on changes of state in things like your database, analytics and auth environment.

We've got just the one speaker this month - giving plenty of opportunities for Q&A afterwards in the library and the pub!

Our sponsors this month are Nagra Media UK (https://www.nagra.com/) and Acorn Recruitment (http://www.acornpeople.com/)

The talks won't start until 17:45 - 18:00 though, so don't worry if you can't make it until a little later. Once our speakers have finished we'll head across to a pub for a couple of drinks and a chat about the evening.

events.name: Google Developer Group (GDG) Cardiff - November
events.description:
Join us for the next Google Developer Group / GDG Cardiff!

The Great GDG Cardiff Pub Quiz!

events.name: Google Developer Group (GDG) Cardiff - February (Assistant API CodeLab)
events.description:
Join us for the next Google Developer Group / GDG Cardiff!

A belated Happy New Year to you all. The longest payday of the year is finally over. To celebrate, and bring back our roots, we're doing something a little different.

No speakers, just hands on development with a few Google home units through a CodeLab (see: https://codelabs.developers.google.com).

Specifically, we're going to be playing with the Assistant API and build a few simple Assistant apps through Actions on Google (see: https://developers.google.com/actions/). How the app looks, feels, and works is all down to you.

What you need to bring:
* A laptop if you have one (recommended, but not essential as there will be teams to join)
* Ideas on what makes an engaging Assistant app

Feel free to play with the simulator and make your own app here: https://console.actions.google.com/ before you attend. If you've not used this API before, your in for a treat.

We look forward to welcoming you. Refreshments will be available as always.

Our sponsors this month are Nagra Media UK (https://www.nagra.com/) and Acorn Recruitment (http://www.acornpeople.com/)

We'll be welcoming people from 17:00, giving you a chance to network with other developers from around Cardiff. We'll be looking to kick off the CodeLab at 17:30 to give enough time for teams to form.
events.how_to_find_us: We're on the top floor of the library, ask at reception and they'll point you our way

events.name: Next '18 Extended Cardiff
events.description:
Catch up with highlights from the Google Cloud Next ’18 conference and learn how to use Google Cloud for AI.

Next ’18 is taking place in San Francisco, but "Extended" events are being held around the world to share the experience.

The Cardiff event will also include a hands-on lab using Qwiklabs to introduce you to Machine Learning with Google Cloud. You'll learn how to deploy a TensorFlow model to Cloud ML Engine and perform sentiment analysis using Cloud Natural Language API.

Bring a laptop if you'd like to join in the Qwiklabs session, otherwise you can watch on the main screen.

All attendees will get 1 month free on Qwiklabs, so you can keep the learning going afterwards.

TL;DR
Pizza and drinks will be provided
5pm: Conference highlights
6pm: Machine Learning introductory labs

events.name: What's new with AI in Google - Laurence Moroney
events.description:
In this talk, Laurence Moroney from the Google Brain team will talk about
AI, Machine Learning and TensorFlow.

He'll cut through the hype and give a programmers perspective of what it's all about. Hear about the latest and greatest in Google AI and where it's going and see some demos of AI apps on Mobile and maybe even IoT.

Laurence is a Developer Advocate at Google, an experienced speaker at events around the world, an author of several technology (and Sci-Fi) books and host of the YouTube show "Coffee with a Googler"
events.how_to_find_us: Top floor, at the back (in the Creative Suite)

events.name: Merry Quizmas! with Cloud Native Wales and AI Wales @ Tramshed Tech
events.description:
Lightning Talks and a Pub Quiz - brought to you by 3 meetups!

It's the season for socialising, so we're cosying up with Cloud Native Wales and AI Wales to see out the year in style.

Spaces are limited, so be considerate with your RSVP (s'il vous plait)

events.name: We don't need another hero
events.description:
We don't need another hero - we just need DevOps
+ Site Reliability Engineering (Lightning Talk)

Does your organisation rely on a Software Superheroes? Brilliant individuals with ten times the mental capacity of normal people, they thrive on late nights and fix the problems that mere mortals cannot.

In our main talk of the evening, Cheryl MacDonald, Head of Engineering at Nagra Media, will discuss the dark side of relying on Software Superheroes and how DevOps can remove the need for heroics.

She will talk about the DevOps journey at Nagra as they transform their on-premise PayTV platform to PayTV as a Service using AWS cloud and move to a fully automated Continuous Delivery pipeline.

About the Meetup

In addition to the main talk, we have a Lightning Talk by James Reed.
James is a Senior Consultant at DevOps Group with 20 years of experience in Development and Operations. He'll be discussing the principles of Site Reliability Engineering (Google "open soruce implementation" of DevOps).

As usual, food and drinks will be provided
After meetup drinks will be in the YARD from 7pm(ish)
events.how_to_find_us: Top Floor, right at the back

events.name: Cloud Study Jam - Kubernetes on Google Cloud
events.description:
Want to get started on the Google Cloud, but don't know where to begin? Join us for our Cloud Study Jam!

Get official Google training, a $55+ value, free of charge. Together we'll work through any (or all) of 3 Google Cloud labs. You will get hands-on experience with the Cloud Console and Kubernetes.

https://blog.qwiklabs.com/study-jam-k8s1/
(access code will be provided at the meetup)

Bring a laptop and charger (PC, Mac or Chromebook)! The labs will run on all of the latest versions of the popular browsers. For the best
experience, make sure your laptop has Firefox or Chrome installed. Don’t forget your charger.

Agenda
17:30 - 18:20: Pitch up and start a lab
18:30 - 18:40: There are no stupid questions (help me I'm stuck!)
18:40 - 19:30: More labs (oh, now I get it!)
19:30: Go home or go to The Yard for a drink... you decide

events.name: Google I/O Extended + Code Lab
events.description:
Google I/O is sure to be full of big announcments this year (remember last year's hairdresser booking demo by the AI assistant?)

Come catch up with the highlights and try out the latest and greatest Google technologies with some I/O code labs (https://events.google.com/io/codelabs/).

Bring a laptop if you want to get hands on with any of the labs - or be lazy and munch pizza while you watch us try to write our first Flutter App, what can go wrong...

Agenda
5.30 - 6.30: Google I/O: the highlights - plus Next '19 gossip
6.30 - 7.30: To the codelab!
7.30: To the pub! (usual debrief at The Yard)

events.name: Another GDG Meetup (AGM)
events.description:
